The new Apple MacBook Air is now available to purchase from iStore South Africa. The slim and powerful notebook was previously available for pre-order and will now start shipping to customers. There are two models of the 13-inch laptop available on the iStore website, one with 128GB of solid state storage and the other with 256GB. Apple first announced its new MacBook Air at the end of October, touting its improved processing capabilities and slimmer, lighter design. Key features of the new MacBook Air include improved battery life, an 8th-gen Intel Core i5 processor, and up to 16GB of DDR4 RAM. The design of the device has also been updated to include a fingerprint sensor and Force Touch trackpad with increased surface area. Below is the South African pricing for the New MacBook Air, which is available from iStore South Africa.